    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Decorative arts style for furnishings pioneered by designer and architect Thomas Jeckyll (1827-1881) and featuring Japanese-inspired ornamentations (both geometric and floral).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046892/Grove Art Online (2003-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estilo de arte decorativo para muebles promovido por el diseñador y arquitecto Thomas Jeckyll (1827-1881), con características ornamentales de inspiración japonesa (tanto geométrica como floral).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type decoratieve kunst voor woninginrichting met als wegbereider de ontwerper en architect Thomas Jeckyll (1827-1881); kenmerkend voor deze stijl zijn de op Japanse motieven geënte ornamenten (zowel geometrische motieven als bloemmotieven).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>傢俱的裝飾藝術風格，此風格的先鋒是設計師和建築師湯瑪斯．傑凱爾（1827-1881）。其特色為受日本風格啟發的裝飾（包括幾何與花卉圖形）。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
